# Target material and thickness variation

target_thickness <- c(0.294, 0.3, 0.44, 1.02, 0.627)

# Pulse width and energy scaling
pulse_width <- c(30, 500, 30, 500, 30)
energy <- c(2.319, 6.0, 132.03, 22.275, 2.358)

# Spot size and intensity control
spot_size <- c(3.3, 4.348, 3.495, 2.13, 3.3)
intensity <- c(6.266e20, 2.759e20, 1.862e21, 4.153e19, 5.10e20)
power <- c(7.756e13, 2.008e14, 4.842e14, 1.76e11, 6.23e13)

# Cutoff energy calculation
cutoff_energy <- c(4.07e2, 1.69e4, 2.58e2, 4.98e1, 1.36e2)

# Create a complete array of 25 samples
data_array <- array(c(target_material, target_thickness, pulse_width, energy, spot_size, intensity, power, cutoff_energy), dim = c(25, 9))

# Display the generated samples
data_array

})
